# ESPerto Test Directory üß™

This directory contains all Python-based unit and integration tests for the ESPerto project.

## How to Run Tests

- **Windows (PowerShell):**

  ```pwsh
  ./scripts/test/run-test.ps1
  ```

- **Linux/macOS:**

  ```sh
  ./scripts/test/run-test.sh
  ```

These scripts will automatically create and activate a Python virtual environment if needed, and install all dependencies from `requirements.txt`.

## Test Frameworks

- [pytest](https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/)
- [pytest-embedded](https://github.com/espressif/pytest-embedded) (for ESP32/ESP-IDF integration)

## Writing Tests

- Place new test files in this directory, using the `test_*.py` naming convention.
- Use `@pytest.mark.esp32` for tests that require ESP32/ESP-IDF context.

## More Information

- [PlatformIO Unit Testing](https://docs.platformio.org/en/latest/advanced/unit-testing/index.html)
- [pytest-embedded Documentation](https://github.com/espressif/pytest-embedded)

